WEBVTT

00:06.702 --> 00:09.183
Previously on
"Kevin Can F... Himself"...[Car horn honks]

00:09.226 --> 00:11.489
Kevin is going
to die.
Yes.

00:11.533 --> 00:12.708
Okay, I can do it.

00:12.751 --> 00:14.666
I thought we weren't
gonna do this anymore.

00:14.710 --> 00:16.451
No, you didn't.

00:16.494 --> 00:19.149
You just need to
broaden your horizons.

00:19.193 --> 00:21.064
She likes me.
We can use that.

00:21.108 --> 00:22.239
Jesus Christ,
what the hell
is happening?

00:22.283 --> 00:23.893
[Both grunting][Spits]

00:23.936 --> 00:25.634
Augh!
You saved my life.

00:25.677 --> 00:28.767
♪

00:28.811 --> 00:30.247
Allison.
Oh.

00:30.291 --> 00:31.596
Is there a problem?No.

00:31.640 --> 00:33.468
Things okay here?Oh, Jesus, Sam.

00:33.511 --> 00:36.036
You do it my way,
or you don't get the money.

00:37.124 --> 00:41.606
♪

00:41.650 --> 00:43.086
Next Saturday.

00:43.130 --> 00:44.914
Next Saturday?
[Scoffs]

00:44.957 --> 00:46.437
You know you don't need
an appointment, right?

00:46.481 --> 00:47.917
I can have this
taken care of today.

00:47.960 --> 00:49.440
No. No, no, I still need
a little more time

00:49.484 --> 00:51.877
to get
a few things in order.

00:51.921 --> 00:54.097
Next week, I'm gonna go visit
my mother in South Carolina,

00:54.141 --> 00:55.490
which I do
every year at this time,

00:55.533 --> 00:56.752
so that gets me
out of Dodge.

00:56.795 --> 00:58.145
With me gone Saturday,

00:58.188 --> 00:59.885
Kevin's gonna be
in full bachelor mode,

00:59.929 --> 01:02.366
which means he's gonna be
blacked out by 11:00,

01:02.410 --> 01:04.499
and when he's out,
he is out.

01:04.542 --> 01:06.979
So, you know...
make it look like a robbery,

01:07.023 --> 01:10.331
and obviously, don't actually
take any of our stuff.

01:10.374 --> 01:13.116
Or -- Okay, yeah.
Take whatever you want.

01:13.160 --> 01:14.987
Our bedroom is top of the stairs
on the left,

01:15.031 --> 01:19.383
and I'm guessing that
you know what to do after that.

01:19.427 --> 01:21.255
You do, right?

01:21.298 --> 01:23.213
Yes! Jesus!

01:23.257 --> 01:25.172
[Inhales sharply]

01:25.215 --> 01:26.434
Good.

01:29.654 --> 01:32.004
So, uh...

01:32.048 --> 01:34.703
what are you
gonna do after?

01:34.746 --> 01:37.619
I'm gonna haul ass
outta your house.

01:37.662 --> 01:39.925
Oh, no, sorry.
I mean, like, after after.

01:39.969 --> 01:41.188
You know?
It's a lot of money.

01:41.231 --> 01:45.017
Do you have any --
any big plans, or...

01:45.061 --> 01:48.108
Getting the hell away from here
the second my parole's up.

01:48.151 --> 01:49.370
[Sighs]

01:49.413 --> 01:51.981
Tell me about it.
[Chuckles]

01:54.244 --> 01:55.245
Yeah.

01:55.289 --> 01:57.813
So, eh, Saturday.

01:57.856 --> 01:59.467
Saturday, and, um...

01:59.510 --> 02:01.817
soon as it's done,
you'll get the money.

02:01.860 --> 02:04.950
So, $7,000 can get you
pretty far.

02:04.994 --> 02:07.039
Not far enough.

02:07.083 --> 02:10.173
[Door opens, creaks]

02:10.217 --> 02:12.001
[Door closes]

02:12.044 --> 02:13.698
Hey.
Hmm?

02:13.742 --> 02:15.352
Customer sent this back.What? Why?

02:15.396 --> 02:17.224
She says
it's not dairy free.

02:17.267 --> 02:18.877
The sauce --
it's gorgonzola.

02:18.921 --> 02:20.575
That's cheese,
you dumbass.

02:20.618 --> 02:22.098
Who gives a shit?Who -- [Scoffs]

02:22.142 --> 02:24.361
That's a whole new fillet
I gotta make, Nicky.

02:24.405 --> 02:25.319
I don't have time
for this.Excuse me --

02:25.362 --> 02:26.537
Oh! Jesus!

02:26.581 --> 02:27.886
I'm sorry, man.
I'm sorry.

02:27.930 --> 02:29.845
Shit![Screams]

02:29.888 --> 02:31.673
Get some ice!
Some ice!

02:31.716 --> 02:33.501
Aah!

02:33.544 --> 02:34.502
Greg: Nick.

02:34.545 --> 02:35.416
What?

02:35.459 --> 02:36.591
"What?"

02:36.634 --> 02:37.722
Christ.

02:37.766 --> 02:39.724
It was an accident.
Yeah?

02:39.768 --> 02:41.117
Now I have
to shut down the grill

02:41.161 --> 02:43.206
till I can scrape
Zack's forearm off it.

02:43.250 --> 02:45.295
Go home.
You can't fire me.

02:45.339 --> 02:47.384
They'll throw me in prison.
You really gonna do that?

02:47.428 --> 02:49.430
Spare me, okay?
That was an assault.

02:49.473 --> 02:52.476
As far as I'm concerned,
Walpole can have you.

02:52.520 --> 02:54.565
[Sighs] Just...

02:54.609 --> 02:56.306
Can I at least
have a day?

02:56.350 --> 02:59.657
A day before my parole officer
finds out about this? Okay?

02:59.701 --> 03:01.268
Do you think
you're in a position

03:01.311 --> 03:04.445
to negotiate right now?

03:04.488 --> 03:06.186
Do you?

03:09.276 --> 03:11.147
Okay. Fine.

03:11.191 --> 03:12.714
Tomorrow morning,
I'm updating

03:12.757 --> 03:15.282
your employment status
with the county.

03:15.325 --> 03:22.463
♪

03:22.506 --> 03:29.644
♪

03:29.687 --> 03:36.868
♪

03:36.912 --> 03:39.306
[Cellphone rings]

03:39.349 --> 03:42.613
♪

03:42.657 --> 03:43.832
Hey, change of plans.

03:43.875 --> 03:46.356
We're leaving tonight.

03:46.400 --> 03:48.880
I just have one thing
I need to take care of first.

03:48.924 --> 03:51.274
[Inhales deeply]

03:51.318 --> 03:53.320
[Laughter]

03:53.363 --> 03:55.670
[Electricity crackles]

03:55.713 --> 03:58.629
[High-pitched ringing]

03:58.673 --> 04:02.416
[Laughter intensifies]

04:04.331 --> 04:07.334
[Indistinct conversations
in distance]

04:07.377 --> 04:11.512
[Siren wails in distance]

04:11.555 --> 04:16.560
♪

04:16.604 --> 04:21.565
♪

04:21.609 --> 04:23.350
Tammy: Allison.

04:23.393 --> 04:25.787
I can only imagine
how traumatic tonight was,

04:25.830 --> 04:27.919
but we're gonna have to ask you
some questions.

04:27.963 --> 04:29.530
Is that alright?

04:31.967 --> 04:35.623
Where were you tonight,
just before the shooting?

04:35.666 --> 04:37.015
I was --
[Clears throat]

04:37.059 --> 04:38.321
I was in bed with Kevin.

04:38.365 --> 04:40.323
And just
for the record --

04:40.367 --> 04:42.543
your relationship
to Kevin McRoberts?

04:42.586 --> 04:45.328
♪

04:45.372 --> 04:47.635
I'm his wife.

04:47.678 --> 04:50.638
I'm his miserable,
pathetic wife,

04:50.681 --> 04:53.336
and I'm so glad he's dead.

04:53.380 --> 04:55.251
Hey!

04:55.295 --> 04:56.557
You can just go home now

04:56.600 --> 04:57.993
if you're not
gonna take this serious.

04:58.036 --> 04:59.647
Well, I am serious.

04:59.690 --> 05:01.388
Oh, yeah?

05:01.431 --> 05:03.259
You'd tell a detective
that you're super glad

05:03.303 --> 05:05.348
your husband has just been
suspiciously murdered?

05:05.392 --> 05:07.698
No, of course not,
but this just seems --

05:07.742 --> 05:09.352
it seems unnecessary.

05:09.396 --> 05:10.962
You love a planning phase,
right?

05:11.006 --> 05:12.486
Well, here we are.

05:12.529 --> 05:14.270
Well, I'm not an idiot.

05:14.314 --> 05:16.141
I have planned, okay?

05:16.185 --> 05:18.492
In a few days, I'm gonna go
see your friend Nick --

05:18.535 --> 05:20.015
Not my friend.
Okay.

05:20.058 --> 05:21.451
Well, you know what I mean.
Your acquaintance --

05:21.495 --> 05:22.713
Not even that.

05:22.757 --> 05:24.846
Your best friend Nick,

05:24.889 --> 05:26.935
and we're gonna go
through all the details,

05:26.978 --> 05:28.589
and then
when the police investigate,

05:28.632 --> 05:30.678
they're gonna find
what we planted as proof

05:30.721 --> 05:32.593
that Kevin is the drug dealer
they're looking for.

05:32.636 --> 05:34.290
You're good.
I'm good.

05:34.334 --> 05:36.205
Done.

05:36.248 --> 05:37.598
Done?

05:37.641 --> 05:39.077
You realize
we're not even

05:39.121 --> 05:42.211
at the hard part of all this,
right?

05:42.254 --> 05:44.387
Sure.

05:44.431 --> 05:47.259
Once Kevin's gone,
that's like the beginning.

05:47.303 --> 05:48.957
You can't just pick up

05:49.000 --> 05:51.351
and go live out
your scone-and-a-book fantasy

05:51.394 --> 05:53.353
the minute the funeral cold cuts
are gone.

05:53.396 --> 05:55.616
Even when a death
isn't suspicious,

05:55.659 --> 05:56.965
people are always
looking to make sure

05:57.008 --> 05:58.662
you're mourning enough.

05:58.706 --> 06:00.490
And with this...

06:00.534 --> 06:02.840
[Sighs] they're gonna have
a ton of questions.

06:02.884 --> 06:04.364
Did you know
he was a drug dealer?

06:04.407 --> 06:06.061
Were you in on the dealing?
How was the marriage?

06:06.104 --> 06:08.280
Did you love him?Okay!

06:08.324 --> 06:10.935
Just because I haven't discussed
every little thing with you

06:10.979 --> 06:12.633
doesn't mean that
I'm not taking this seriously

06:12.676 --> 06:14.156
or that I'm some kind
of big idiot.

06:14.199 --> 06:16.724
Well, screwing your boss
seems pretty idiotic.

06:22.207 --> 06:23.383
Yeah.

06:23.426 --> 06:25.820
I know.

06:25.863 --> 06:29.258
And I found out
with just about zero effort.

06:29.301 --> 06:30.694
If I did,

06:30.738 --> 06:32.957
I can only guess
the cops will, too.

06:33.001 --> 06:35.307
Do you really think
that's a good move right now?

06:35.351 --> 06:37.614
I didn't think of it as a move.
It just happened.

06:37.658 --> 06:41.531
Things can't
"just happen."

06:41.575 --> 06:44.621
Everything you're doing
right now is gonna be judged.

06:44.665 --> 06:46.014
If you're laughing
at his jokes.

06:46.057 --> 06:47.450
What you're buying
at the damn grocery store.

06:47.494 --> 06:48.538
It all sends a message,

06:48.582 --> 06:50.714
and what do you think
affair says?

06:50.758 --> 06:52.586
It's...

06:52.629 --> 06:54.109
bad.

06:54.152 --> 06:55.415
Yes.

06:57.765 --> 07:00.158
Listen, I...

07:00.202 --> 07:02.030
I know you don't want
to think ahead

07:02.073 --> 07:03.118
'cause it makes it real.

07:03.161 --> 07:04.772
It's not that.
No, it is.

07:04.815 --> 07:07.557
And I get it.

07:07.601 --> 07:10.647
But closing your eyes to reality
doesn't change anything.

07:10.691 --> 07:13.433
It just makes you blind.

07:15.391 --> 07:17.611
So, you gotta be
smarter than this.

07:17.654 --> 07:19.917
Smarter than having an affair
right now --

07:19.961 --> 07:22.529
I know!

07:22.572 --> 07:24.879
I know. I know. I know.

07:24.922 --> 07:26.097
[Inhales deeply]

07:26.141 --> 07:28.578
[Sighs shakily]

07:28.622 --> 07:31.755
Hey.

07:31.799 --> 07:33.583
Eyes open.

07:33.627 --> 07:36.717
♪

07:36.760 --> 07:37.979
Right?

07:38.022 --> 07:44.420
♪

07:44.464 --> 07:45.987
Now...

07:48.816 --> 07:52.341
...what is your relationship
to Kevin McRoberts?

07:52.384 --> 08:01.176
♪

08:01.219 --> 08:03.134
He was my husband,

08:03.178 --> 08:05.876
and I loved him
more than anything.

08:05.920 --> 08:08.488
Sam, I can't do this.

08:08.531 --> 08:09.663
Yeah, you know what?

08:09.706 --> 08:11.578
This isn't working for me,
either.

08:11.621 --> 08:12.840
No, I'm serious.
I'm serious.

08:12.883 --> 08:14.319
I --

08:14.363 --> 08:15.930
I've been thinking,
and I need to f--

08:15.973 --> 08:18.802
to focus on my marriage.

08:18.846 --> 08:20.369
[Chuckles] Uh...

08:24.373 --> 08:25.766
Your marriage?

08:25.809 --> 08:26.984
You hate your husband.I don't.

08:27.028 --> 08:28.986
I don't --
I don't hate him.

08:29.030 --> 08:30.422
I've just been...

08:30.466 --> 08:31.641
I've been confused.

08:31.685 --> 08:33.774
No, you haven't
been confused.

08:33.817 --> 08:35.253
You've been very clear --

08:35.297 --> 08:37.038
You're miserable.
Okay.

08:37.081 --> 08:38.909
Do you think telling me that I'm
wrong's gonna change my mind?

08:38.953 --> 08:40.607
That's not how this works,
okay?

08:40.650 --> 08:42.696
I-I said I'm done.
I'm done.

08:42.739 --> 08:43.697
Okay, wait.

08:43.740 --> 08:45.350
Sam, stop.
No. No.

08:45.394 --> 08:47.744
Not until I understand what
the hell just happened here.

08:47.788 --> 08:50.747
Um, 30 seconds ago,
we were fine.

08:50.791 --> 08:53.663
And now we're just what?
Over?

08:53.707 --> 08:56.318
I told you,
I love my husband,

08:56.361 --> 08:58.799
and I need
to make it work.

08:58.842 --> 09:00.583
So, you're just gonna
throw us away --

09:00.627 --> 09:02.324
for Kevin?

09:02.367 --> 09:04.065
"Us"?

09:04.108 --> 09:06.807
We're not some big love story.
You're my boss.

09:06.850 --> 09:09.026
We have sex in a --
in a...closet.

09:09.070 --> 09:11.420
No, you know
it's more than that.

09:11.463 --> 09:13.901
No, we pretend that it is
because we don't want

09:13.944 --> 09:15.380
to acknowledge
the boring truth,

09:15.424 --> 09:17.208
which is that we're two...

09:17.252 --> 09:18.949
tired, shitty people

09:18.993 --> 09:21.082
who just needed
to feel something.

09:23.519 --> 09:25.565
Do you feel...

09:25.608 --> 09:27.044
anything?

09:31.266 --> 09:33.137
Well...

09:33.181 --> 09:36.706
thank you, I guess.

09:36.750 --> 09:40.057
Suddenly, I'm more than happy
to never do this again,

09:40.101 --> 09:43.583
because you...

09:43.626 --> 09:46.063
I don't know when
you got so...

09:46.107 --> 09:47.761
broken.

09:54.637 --> 09:56.291
[Gasps]

09:56.334 --> 09:59.468
[Voice breaking]
Oh, what the hell?

10:01.209 --> 10:02.689
[Inhales sharply]Wick: You okay?

10:02.732 --> 10:04.386
Mm-hmm.
Sure.

10:04.429 --> 10:05.648
You know,
you don't need to be brave.

10:05.692 --> 10:07.607
I see 15 women a day,
and they all look

10:07.650 --> 10:08.695
the same way
that you do right now.

10:08.738 --> 10:09.826
Mm-hmm.

10:09.870 --> 10:12.307
And how do I look?
Nervous.

10:12.350 --> 10:14.178
Like you're about to find out
you're defective.

10:14.222 --> 10:16.224
But if the bloodwork
comes back okay,

10:16.267 --> 10:18.574
then we will find a way
to make it happen.

10:18.618 --> 10:20.881
It's what I'm here for.
You'll get your baby.

10:24.580 --> 10:27.888
Um, and it'll be clear that
I'm here for fertility stuff,

10:27.931 --> 10:30.238
like on some
official record?

10:30.281 --> 10:32.414
Hmm?
My, um...

10:32.457 --> 10:35.112
My insurance company can be
a real pain.
Oh, yeah.

10:35.156 --> 10:37.114
The -- The girls up front
will get them what they need.

10:37.158 --> 10:39.073
Alright.
Little pressure here.

10:39.116 --> 10:40.291
[Groans]

10:40.335 --> 10:42.424
So this will be
your first?

10:42.467 --> 10:43.730
Yeah.

10:43.773 --> 10:46.341
And how long have you been
with your partner?

10:46.384 --> 10:47.908
My husband.

10:47.951 --> 10:50.606
My wonderful husband.

10:50.650 --> 10:53.696
I-I met him when I was 20,
and since then,

10:53.740 --> 10:56.568
I feel like I've been
in some kind of fever dream.

10:56.612 --> 10:58.005
A greatone.

10:58.048 --> 10:59.615
That's young.

10:59.659 --> 11:02.052
Yeah.

11:02.096 --> 11:04.489
I was so nervous
on my wedding day.

11:04.533 --> 11:07.623
I'm -- I'm not good with crowds
or big decisions.

11:07.667 --> 11:08.842
[Laughs]

11:08.885 --> 11:11.148
I just kept...
reapplying deodorant

11:11.192 --> 11:14.674
and wondering if I should
just run for the hills.

11:14.717 --> 11:16.153
He saw me, uh...

11:16.197 --> 11:17.502
pacing back and forth
in the hallway,

11:17.546 --> 11:20.984
almost crying
to Father O'Donnell.

11:21.028 --> 11:23.073
I'm sure it was obvious
I was freaking out,

11:23.117 --> 11:25.162
but instead of talking to me
about it

11:25.206 --> 11:27.687
or acknowledging it,
he, uh...

11:27.730 --> 11:30.298
[Laughs]

11:30.341 --> 11:33.736
He pantsed the priest.

11:33.780 --> 11:35.825
I actually laughed.

11:35.869 --> 11:37.348
And after that,
I was fine,

11:37.392 --> 11:39.742
because I-I really believed
that he would --

11:39.786 --> 11:42.266
you know, he would do
anything for me.

11:42.310 --> 11:45.226
Just keep...
pantsing priests

11:45.269 --> 11:48.533
and making me laugh
for the rest of our lives.

11:48.577 --> 11:50.797
I haven't thought about that
in years.

11:53.451 --> 11:54.757
Well, it's a good thing
you didn't wait

11:54.801 --> 11:56.628
another 15 years
to start trying.

11:56.672 --> 11:59.675
Nobody's getting
any younger.

11:59.719 --> 12:01.633
[Sobs]

12:01.677 --> 12:03.070
Oh, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean --

12:03.113 --> 12:04.854
No, I'm fine.

12:04.898 --> 12:07.378
I'm fine.
I'm not usually a --

12:07.422 --> 12:10.425
I'm not usually emotional,
so I'm fine.

12:12.819 --> 12:14.385
I'll be fine.

12:18.650 --> 12:20.261
Thank you.

12:20.304 --> 12:22.654
Uh, will there be
a record of my visit.

12:22.698 --> 12:24.569
Just my, uh...
My insurance company --

12:24.613 --> 12:26.006
You bet.

12:26.049 --> 12:28.922
[Telephone rings in distance]

12:28.965 --> 12:30.053
'Kay.

12:33.361 --> 12:35.450
[Sighing] Mm.

12:35.493 --> 12:37.408
Ah!

12:39.497 --> 12:41.238
[Chuckles]

12:42.326 --> 12:44.198
[Clears throat loudly]

12:50.117 --> 12:51.945
Oh! Oh.

12:51.988 --> 12:54.382
[Chuckles]

12:54.425 --> 12:56.210
Sorry.

12:56.253 --> 12:57.864
Classic Allison.

12:57.907 --> 13:04.044
♪

13:04.087 --> 13:06.220
[Telephone rings in distance]

13:06.263 --> 13:08.048
Well...

13:08.091 --> 13:10.267
so cute.

13:10.311 --> 13:12.313
Can't wait to show my husband
when I get home.

13:12.356 --> 13:17.884
♪

13:17.927 --> 13:20.408
[Sobs]

13:20.451 --> 13:22.976
Damn it!

13:24.760 --> 13:31.027
♪

13:31.071 --> 13:32.507
Tammy: Can you tell me
what happened

13:32.550 --> 13:35.858
immediately after
you heard the gunshot?

13:35.902 --> 13:37.729
Um...

13:37.773 --> 13:40.515
I don't know.

13:40.558 --> 13:43.213
There was screaming.

13:43.257 --> 13:44.475
And...

13:44.519 --> 13:46.564
our neighbor called.

13:46.608 --> 13:47.739
Patty.

13:47.783 --> 13:49.176
Well, you know Patty.

13:49.219 --> 13:53.180
♪

13:53.223 --> 13:56.705
Patty's full name, please?

13:56.748 --> 13:58.402
Um, sure.

13:58.446 --> 14:01.928
Um,
Patricia Deirdre O'Connor.

14:01.971 --> 14:04.539
[Classical music plays]

14:08.325 --> 14:10.588
Oh, hell.

14:10.632 --> 14:12.460
You need some help?

14:12.503 --> 14:13.896
No. No.

14:13.940 --> 14:15.419
I'm fine.

14:15.463 --> 14:17.813
This is great.
It's a great date.

14:20.250 --> 14:21.382
Ahh!

14:21.425 --> 14:23.819
Wow.
You hate this.

14:23.863 --> 14:25.429
No.

14:25.473 --> 14:26.996
I --
Thank God.

14:27.040 --> 14:28.780
Me, too.

14:28.824 --> 14:31.218
I thought this was gonna
be soothing or something.

14:31.261 --> 14:33.568
It's not.

14:33.611 --> 14:36.353
Want to just get drunk off
their wedding wine?

14:38.225 --> 14:40.923
Yes, please.

14:40.967 --> 14:42.707
Ooh.

14:44.971 --> 14:47.234
I love your brush strokes here.
Very evocative.

14:47.277 --> 14:49.323
Oh, yeah?
Absolutely.

14:49.366 --> 14:52.326
I can feel your anger
at the sunset.

14:52.369 --> 14:54.415
It's a commentary
on the passage of time.

14:54.458 --> 14:57.461
Of course.
Where you gonna put it?

14:57.505 --> 14:59.289
Somewhere
really special.

14:59.333 --> 15:01.683
[Cellphone vibrates]

15:01.726 --> 15:03.119
[Laughs]

15:03.163 --> 15:04.294
Sorry.

15:04.338 --> 15:06.209
This is rude.

15:06.253 --> 15:09.169
But work is intense.

15:09.212 --> 15:11.519
Anything interesting?

15:11.562 --> 15:13.738
Maybe.

15:13.782 --> 15:15.566
Come on.

15:15.610 --> 15:17.438
Liven up the life
of a hairdresser, please.

15:17.481 --> 15:20.354
[Scoffs] I'm not sure
how exciting it is.

15:20.397 --> 15:22.051
We picked up this
little old lady

15:22.095 --> 15:24.967
for a forged prescription
across town at Melba's.

15:25.011 --> 15:26.969
Like, a 98-year-old
telling me and Bram

15:27.013 --> 15:28.971
to screw off.
[Chuckles]

15:29.015 --> 15:30.842
But I'm pretty sure
she was being supplied

15:30.886 --> 15:34.368
by this dealer we're after,
so...

15:34.411 --> 15:35.586
Done.

15:35.630 --> 15:37.545
All yours again.

15:40.852 --> 15:43.681
Um...

15:43.725 --> 15:45.509
my brother might
be in there.

15:45.553 --> 15:47.250
He uses my oven a lot.

15:47.294 --> 15:48.991
I've met Neil.

15:49.035 --> 15:51.211
I don't think you have to worry
about him deducing anything.

15:51.254 --> 15:52.299
Yeah.

15:54.301 --> 15:55.955
But it's not just Neil
you're worried about.

15:58.218 --> 16:00.481
This has all just happened
kinda fast,

16:00.524 --> 16:02.613
and I haven't been able
to get my head around it.

16:02.657 --> 16:05.138
What's to get
your head around?

16:05.181 --> 16:06.748
We like each other.

16:06.791 --> 16:08.837
Yeah.

16:08.880 --> 16:11.100
And that's new for me.

16:11.144 --> 16:13.973
Is it?
Come on.

16:14.016 --> 16:15.061
You're telling me
I'm the first woman

16:15.104 --> 16:17.802
you've ever had
feelings for?

16:17.846 --> 16:19.848
I...

16:19.891 --> 16:22.329
guess so.

16:22.372 --> 16:23.547
Yeah. Yes.

16:23.591 --> 16:25.158
You didn't grow up
looking twice

16:25.201 --> 16:27.856
at the Morton's Salt Girl
or Jo from "Facts of Life"?

16:27.899 --> 16:30.380
What? No.

16:30.424 --> 16:33.079
Are you much older
than me?

16:33.122 --> 16:34.602
What about your
"nosy ass neighbor"

16:34.645 --> 16:36.865
from the bar
the other night?

16:36.908 --> 16:39.085
Okay. Now you don't know
what you're talking about,

16:39.128 --> 16:40.564
so you should just stop.

16:40.608 --> 16:42.175
I'm not trying
to piss you off.

16:42.218 --> 16:43.828
I'm just trying to show you
that it's not a big deal.

16:43.872 --> 16:46.048
Maybe it is.

16:46.092 --> 16:48.355
I have cable, okay?

16:48.398 --> 16:52.402
I know we're all fine
with everything now,

16:52.446 --> 16:55.318
but maybe if you're 33
and still figuring things out,

16:55.362 --> 16:57.712
it's...

16:57.755 --> 17:01.237
it's embarrassing.

17:01.281 --> 17:05.067
Can you please
just let it be hard?

17:05.111 --> 17:07.026
Can't that be okay?

17:09.028 --> 17:12.422
If it's the right person --
if I'mthe right person --

17:12.466 --> 17:15.338
I think it's supposed
to be easy.

17:15.382 --> 17:17.036
And you'd probably kiss me
before you had a chance

17:17.079 --> 17:20.561
to think about
who might see.

17:20.604 --> 17:26.132
♪

17:26.175 --> 17:31.659
♪

17:31.702 --> 17:32.921
[Sighs]

17:32.964 --> 17:37.186
♪

17:37.230 --> 17:38.709
[Laughter][Camera shutter clicks]

17:38.753 --> 17:41.190
No, I think, uh,
the slashing windmill's

17:41.234 --> 17:42.844
a better look on me, Neil.

17:42.887 --> 17:44.759
[Camera shutter clicks]

17:44.802 --> 17:46.239
Fine.

17:46.282 --> 17:47.457
But I get to stick
my tongue out.

17:47.501 --> 17:49.285
It's very muscular.

17:49.329 --> 17:52.158
[Laughter]

17:52.201 --> 17:55.030
Shouldn't you have gotten this
out of your system at Halloween?

17:55.074 --> 17:56.727
Kev and I are
starting a band.

17:56.771 --> 17:58.120
Shouldn't you have gotten that
out of your system

17:58.164 --> 18:00.035
in middle school?

18:00.079 --> 18:02.777
It is never too late
to fulfill your destiny.

18:02.820 --> 18:04.170
I just found out last night

18:04.213 --> 18:08.087
that I'm supposed
to be a rock star.

18:08.130 --> 18:11.046
Kev did karaoke at Sully's
and killed it.

18:11.090 --> 18:13.701
I always knew I was
destined to be famous.

18:13.744 --> 18:16.138
I just never thought
it'd be for singing.

18:16.182 --> 18:18.880
Yeah, I assumed it'd be some
sort of testicle-bashing video.

18:18.923 --> 18:20.751
Same.

18:20.795 --> 18:23.624
I mean, singing is [Chuckles]
pretty soft, you know?

18:23.667 --> 18:26.366
Yeah.
Thanks, Josh Groban.

18:26.409 --> 18:29.586
But last night,
with the crowd eating it up,

18:29.630 --> 18:31.675
I just figured,
if it leads to fame and fortune,

18:31.719 --> 18:33.503
it can't be that soft.

18:33.547 --> 18:35.157
And that's
when it dawned on me.

18:35.201 --> 18:38.291
♪ Jenny McCarthy
Tank Top ♪

18:38.334 --> 18:42.077
Is that --
What is that?

18:42.121 --> 18:43.687
It's our band name.
Yeah.

18:43.731 --> 18:46.299
Jenny McCarthy Tank Top?

18:46.342 --> 18:48.605
It's brilliant. We'll save
a bundle on marketing.

18:48.649 --> 18:50.477
Yeah, everyone I know
already Googles

18:50.520 --> 18:53.044
"Jenny McCarthy Tank Top"
constantly.

18:53.088 --> 18:55.308
Now our sound
will pop up

18:55.351 --> 18:57.614
right next to the blonde
in the half shirt.

18:57.658 --> 19:01.966
It was either that or...
♪ Fassbender's Hog!

19:02.010 --> 19:05.056
No day jobs.
No responsibilities.

19:05.100 --> 19:07.972
Just the music
and the open road.

19:08.016 --> 19:09.452
And let me guess.

19:09.496 --> 19:12.238
I'm on tambourine.

19:12.281 --> 19:13.456
Uh, oh.

19:13.500 --> 19:15.589
Well...
Uh...

19:15.632 --> 19:19.245
we didn't exactly,
uh, factor you in.

19:19.288 --> 19:20.898
Yeah.

19:20.942 --> 19:23.901
Well, uh, what do you know
about driving a tour bus?

19:23.945 --> 19:25.381
Or -- Or --
Or picking out

19:25.425 --> 19:27.775
only green M&M's
from bags of other M&M's?

19:27.818 --> 19:30.473
Hey, hey, hey.
Hold up.

19:30.517 --> 19:32.171
Band meeting.

19:34.782 --> 19:36.087
Ugh! [Sighs]

19:36.131 --> 19:37.524
We cannot have a girl

19:37.567 --> 19:40.091
in a band named
Jenny McCarthy Tank Top.

19:40.135 --> 19:42.920
I guess that would
be pretty weird.

19:42.964 --> 19:45.401
Unless
it's Jenny McCarthy.

19:45.445 --> 19:47.098
[Laughter]

19:47.142 --> 19:48.491
So we're agreed then?

19:48.535 --> 19:50.232
We put the kibosh
on chicks in the bank

19:50.276 --> 19:51.842
who aren't
Jenny McCarthy?

19:51.886 --> 19:53.279
Even a half-chick
like Patty?

19:53.322 --> 19:56.020
Ugh.

19:56.064 --> 19:59.198
Men: ♪ Jenny McCarthy Tank Top

20:02.592 --> 20:03.811
[Note plays]

20:03.854 --> 20:05.421
I'm sorry, man,

20:05.465 --> 20:07.945
but there's just no room for you
in Jenny McCarthy...

20:07.989 --> 20:09.469
♪ Tank Top ♪ Top

20:09.512 --> 20:11.297
And what about Allison?

20:11.340 --> 20:13.168
She's in the bathroom
getting all dolled up

20:13.212 --> 20:14.256
to be a groupie.

20:14.300 --> 20:15.823
Oh, you know,

20:15.866 --> 20:17.651
I'd say you could be a groupie,
too, Patty,

20:17.694 --> 20:20.088
but you obviously can't
be with Neil, so...

20:20.131 --> 20:21.959
you'd have
to be Pete's.

20:22.003 --> 20:24.005
Too clingy.

20:24.048 --> 20:29.445
♪

20:29.489 --> 20:37.714
[Knocks on door]

20:37.758 --> 20:39.325
Allison?

20:39.368 --> 20:40.587
Patty?

20:40.630 --> 20:41.892
Yes.

20:41.936 --> 20:44.504
Obviously.

20:44.547 --> 20:46.854
What're you doing
in here?

20:46.897 --> 20:48.551
I'm...

20:51.119 --> 20:52.294
[Sniffles]

20:52.338 --> 20:54.340
Jesus, what the hell
happened to you?

20:54.383 --> 20:56.429
Nothing.

20:56.472 --> 20:58.257
Uh...

20:58.300 --> 20:59.432
you sure?

20:59.475 --> 21:00.737
Yeah.
I'm fine.

21:00.781 --> 21:02.826
[Sobbing]

21:02.870 --> 21:04.698
You're sobbing.
No, I'm not.

21:04.741 --> 21:07.527
I'm not.

21:07.570 --> 21:09.529
Last time I cried
was, like, 10 years ago,

21:09.572 --> 21:11.531
and even then,
it was 'cause I saw a dog

21:11.574 --> 21:14.185
get hit by a car
outside the package store.

21:14.229 --> 21:16.971
What,
am I made of stone?

21:17.014 --> 21:19.495
Even Uncle Chuck pretended to
have allergies that day, okay?

21:19.539 --> 21:20.757
[Sobs]

21:20.801 --> 21:22.846
Ugh.
Shut up.

21:22.890 --> 21:24.674
[Sighs deeply]

21:24.718 --> 21:26.415
It's been happening
all week.

21:26.459 --> 21:27.808
It's like
a physical thing.

21:27.851 --> 21:32.073
I can't help it.
It's like a -- a sneeze.

21:32.116 --> 21:33.814
Yeah.

21:33.857 --> 21:36.382
I like to get drunk alone
in the tub to sneeze, too.

21:36.425 --> 21:39.428
I should just get used to it,
right?

21:39.472 --> 21:40.995
"Drunk and alone"
is a nice snapshot

21:41.038 --> 21:42.475
of the rest of my life.

21:42.518 --> 21:45.347
Come on.
No, you come on!

21:45.391 --> 21:47.741
I've done some shit, Patty.

21:47.784 --> 21:50.874
I'm like a monster now.
I-I hurt people.

21:50.918 --> 21:52.876
I lied
to a police officer.

21:52.920 --> 21:55.749
You think that's
the worst thing you've done?

21:55.792 --> 21:57.577
I just risked everything

21:57.620 --> 21:59.535
so that afterwards,
when it's done,

21:59.579 --> 22:01.929
I get to die alone.
Jesus.

22:01.972 --> 22:04.540
And I'm basically
all dried up down there,

22:04.584 --> 22:07.761
so I can't even have kids
to guilt into loving me.

22:07.804 --> 22:09.676
What?

22:09.719 --> 22:12.722
Do you even want kids?

22:12.766 --> 22:14.724
[Sighs]
Of course.

22:14.768 --> 22:17.988
That's what you do.

22:18.032 --> 22:21.078
I just don't want Kevin's.

22:21.122 --> 22:22.341
No. [Snaps fingers]

22:22.384 --> 22:23.559
Hey.

22:23.603 --> 22:25.169
Gimme that.

22:27.041 --> 22:28.999
[Sighs]

22:33.743 --> 22:36.355
I'm broken.

22:36.398 --> 22:37.921
And before all this,

22:37.965 --> 22:39.967
you were the picture
of perfection?

22:40.010 --> 22:41.185
Please.

22:41.229 --> 22:42.404
[Scoffs]

22:42.448 --> 22:44.972
Thank you.

22:45.015 --> 22:47.627
No, I --

22:47.670 --> 22:51.544
I mean, I couldn't stand
being around you before.

22:51.587 --> 22:54.024
You had the presence
of, like, a pointy houseplant.

22:54.068 --> 22:56.157
But a naggy one.
A naggy ficus.

22:56.200 --> 22:58.028
Is this you being nice?

22:58.072 --> 23:00.683
I mean, I came up here
looking for you

23:00.727 --> 23:02.206
not because things
were going to shit

23:02.250 --> 23:05.209
and I had to talk to you,
but because I wanted to.

23:08.778 --> 23:11.651
I'm just --
I'm saying...

23:11.694 --> 23:14.044
if this is you broken...

23:16.656 --> 23:19.528
If this is you broken...

23:19.572 --> 23:21.269
stay broken.

23:27.536 --> 23:28.668
Come on.

23:28.711 --> 23:29.669
What?

23:29.712 --> 23:32.367
Come on.

23:32.411 --> 23:34.500
In there?
Mm-hmm.

23:37.459 --> 23:39.983
[Laughs]
Oh!

23:40.027 --> 23:41.245
Shut up.

23:41.289 --> 23:44.727
[Chuckles]

23:44.771 --> 23:46.425
Hey.

23:50.037 --> 23:53.214
I like talking
to you, too.

23:53.257 --> 23:59.873
♪ Ohhh, oh-h-h

23:59.916 --> 24:02.745
So maybe we can die
alone together.

24:02.789 --> 24:08.751
♪ Oh, my love

24:08.795 --> 24:13.930
♪ Oh, my love

24:13.974 --> 24:16.890
♪ My darling

24:16.933 --> 24:22.330
♪ I've hungered for your touch

24:22.373 --> 24:30.251
♪ A long, lonely time

24:30.294 --> 24:32.775
You are the right person.

24:32.819 --> 24:34.821
You.

24:34.864 --> 24:36.431
Okay?

24:36.475 --> 24:38.912
♪ Ooh, my love

24:38.955 --> 24:41.131
Okay.

24:41.175 --> 24:47.050
♪ Ooh, my love

24:47.094 --> 24:51.925
♪ My love

24:53.840 --> 24:56.190
Bob: Is there anyone you can
think of who's been in conflict

24:56.233 --> 24:57.496
with your husband lately?

24:57.539 --> 25:00.107
Anyone who...
might want to hurt him?

25:00.150 --> 25:03.806
[Sighs] I don't --
Everybody loves Kevin.

25:03.850 --> 25:07.593
Was there an argument
earlier in the day

25:07.636 --> 25:08.855
with a friend of his?

25:08.898 --> 25:10.378
Uh, Neil?

25:10.421 --> 25:12.249
He and the intruder
were on the same hockey team

25:12.293 --> 25:15.426
together at Burncoat.

25:15.470 --> 25:17.167
I mean, maybe.

25:19.518 --> 25:21.302
No, K--

25:21.345 --> 25:23.130
Neil's not capable
of something like this.

25:23.173 --> 25:24.697
You'd be surprised
how dark people can be

25:24.740 --> 25:26.699
beneath the surface.

25:26.742 --> 25:29.005
Oh, no.
I don't mean capable like that.

25:29.049 --> 25:32.008
I mean, um...

25:32.052 --> 25:34.533
You know, the guy
who jumps off a bridge

25:34.576 --> 25:36.447
'cause all of his friends
are doing it?

25:36.491 --> 25:38.275
That's not Neil.

25:38.319 --> 25:41.452
Neil's the guy who offers
to jump in first to see

25:41.496 --> 25:43.150
if the water's too cold.

25:43.193 --> 25:48.982
♪

25:49.025 --> 25:50.636
The heck?

25:50.679 --> 25:53.203
Who's throws
something like this away?

25:53.247 --> 25:56.206
Future album cover art
for Jenny McCarthy Tank Top?

25:56.250 --> 25:58.469
Uh, yes, please!

25:58.513 --> 26:01.647
[Laughter]

26:01.690 --> 26:03.300
[Gasps]

26:03.344 --> 26:07.087
[Laughter]

26:07.130 --> 26:08.610
No, please.

26:08.654 --> 26:10.481
Come on in.

26:10.525 --> 26:12.788
Good morning,
Neil.

26:12.832 --> 26:14.137
Neil?

26:14.181 --> 26:15.356
Good morning?

26:15.399 --> 26:18.098
Oh, hi. So--
I didn't see you.

26:18.141 --> 26:20.187
And your cop friend.

26:20.230 --> 26:22.189
S-Sorry.

26:22.232 --> 26:25.105
At ease.

26:25.148 --> 26:26.497
It's actually great
that you're here.

26:26.541 --> 26:27.890
Can I get your advise
on something?

26:27.934 --> 26:28.848
Move.No!

26:28.891 --> 26:30.153
Leave her alone,
Neil!

26:30.197 --> 26:32.634
No, it's okay.
What you got?

26:32.678 --> 26:34.070
Well, let's just say

26:34.114 --> 26:35.768
you had some evidence
that your co-lead singer

26:35.811 --> 26:37.596
and co-lead guitarist
was doing something sneaky

26:37.639 --> 26:39.206
that could break up
Jenny McCarthy Tank Top

26:39.249 --> 26:40.990
before it even started?

26:41.034 --> 26:43.906
I'm really not following,
Neil.

26:43.950 --> 26:46.779
I found these
in the trash outside.

26:46.822 --> 26:49.912
They're forms and pamphlets
from a baby making clinic.

26:49.956 --> 26:52.132
Pamphlets with babies
on them.

26:52.175 --> 26:54.874
Forms with Allison
on them.

26:54.917 --> 26:56.223
You know what
this means?

26:56.266 --> 26:57.659
That's it's very
personal information,

26:57.703 --> 27:01.228
and you should stay out
of other people's marriages?

27:01.271 --> 27:04.274
No, it means that Kevin's
been lying to me.

27:04.318 --> 27:06.146
So you want to do
an interrogation?

27:06.189 --> 27:07.756
Exactly.
Teach me how.

27:07.800 --> 27:11.151
No, Tammy's off duty.
Leave her alone!

27:11.194 --> 27:12.631
It's okay, Patty.

27:12.674 --> 27:15.721
I don't mind sharing
a little of my expertise.

27:15.764 --> 27:17.026
Great.

27:17.070 --> 27:18.288
So I was thinking
we get him,

27:18.332 --> 27:19.768
and I tie him down
to a chair,

27:19.812 --> 27:24.033
and then I shine a light
in his eyes, real dramatic-like.

27:24.077 --> 27:26.732
Well, that's illegal.

27:26.775 --> 27:28.690
But what we usually do
is make the perp think

27:28.734 --> 27:30.474
we have more evidence
than we do.

27:30.518 --> 27:33.956
By shining a light in his eyes,
real dramatic-like?

27:34.000 --> 27:35.479
Not exactly.

27:35.523 --> 27:37.003
First, we start with
a couple baseline questions

27:37.046 --> 27:38.700
that have nothing to do
with the crime

27:38.744 --> 27:41.050
so we can establish
a good relationship.

27:41.094 --> 27:44.793
"Questions
for good relationship."

27:44.837 --> 27:47.535
Then you should stay quiet
as much as you can.

27:47.578 --> 27:49.450
Stay quiet, as in,
"Don't ask him anything

27:49.493 --> 27:53.062
because it's none
of your business."

27:53.106 --> 27:55.499
As in...
let the perp talk.

27:55.543 --> 27:57.197
And if I have a photo
or a piece of evidence

27:57.240 --> 27:59.503
that I think
might take him by surprise,

27:59.547 --> 28:01.592
I slide it
across the table.

28:01.636 --> 28:04.073
Real...dramatic-like?

28:04.117 --> 28:06.206
Real dramatic-like.

28:08.382 --> 28:09.775
Then I watch
their face.

28:09.818 --> 28:11.646
You're looking
for signs of recognition.

28:11.690 --> 28:13.561
What if this guy's
a real mastermind?

28:13.604 --> 28:16.259
I mean, he once snuck booze
into Gillette Stadium

28:16.303 --> 28:18.522
in a fake fat stomach...

28:18.566 --> 28:22.135
over his real
fat stomach.

28:22.178 --> 28:24.311
What if he outsmarts me,
and I can't tell?

28:24.354 --> 28:26.008
Well,
then my partner and I

28:26.052 --> 28:28.707
would do a little
good cop/bad cop.

28:28.750 --> 28:31.231
Oh! That's good.

28:31.274 --> 28:33.886
"Good cop/bad cop".

28:33.929 --> 28:36.932
Man, you are way funner
than Allison to have around.

28:36.976 --> 28:38.194
Thanks for your help.

28:38.238 --> 28:39.630
Happy interrogating.

28:39.674 --> 28:41.023
Is there
any other kind?

28:41.067 --> 28:42.590
No! Stop.

28:42.633 --> 28:45.811
You can't go getting
into other people's business.

28:45.854 --> 28:47.638
Fine.

28:47.682 --> 28:51.251
[Laughter]

28:53.383 --> 28:55.211
Kevin.

28:55.255 --> 28:57.083
Interesting
to find you here.

28:57.126 --> 28:58.824
Uh, yeah.

28:58.867 --> 29:00.826
Hey,
how's your guitar coming?

29:00.869 --> 29:02.653
'Cause I've been thinking,
it might be cooler

29:02.697 --> 29:04.786
if I just sing
and hold the guitar

29:04.830 --> 29:07.571
and you play
for both of us.

29:07.615 --> 29:09.922
Hey, Kev,
I got a couple of questions.

29:09.965 --> 29:11.706
Okay.

29:11.750 --> 29:15.623
How many beans do you think
are in a standard Bush's can?

29:15.666 --> 29:17.712
I don't know.
Great.

29:17.756 --> 29:20.149
What a fun relationship
we've established.

29:20.193 --> 29:22.064
[Chuckling]
Are you okay?

29:22.108 --> 29:23.849
Did you try to put on
a fake mustache

29:23.892 --> 29:26.503
with airplane glue again?

29:26.547 --> 29:30.507
Kev, listen,
I'm on your team here.

29:30.551 --> 29:32.988
So why don't you tell me
what you need to tell me?

29:33.032 --> 29:34.424
Uh, o-okay.

29:34.468 --> 29:36.252
Uh, I was gonna wait
until Pete got back,

29:36.296 --> 29:38.428
but I guess I can
tell you now.

29:38.472 --> 29:39.821
I booked us a gig
for the band.

29:39.865 --> 29:41.344
Wait, no way.

29:41.388 --> 29:42.911
Really?
That's wicked awesome.

29:42.955 --> 29:45.435
Hey, I got some art
we can use for the poster and --

29:45.479 --> 29:47.002
Mnm, no. No.

29:47.046 --> 29:48.308
That's --
That's not it.

29:48.351 --> 29:49.657
Huh?

29:51.833 --> 29:54.531
Kev, listen,

29:54.575 --> 29:56.664
I'm your friend here,
okay?

29:56.707 --> 29:58.579
You can come clean,

29:58.622 --> 30:00.668
because I'm being nice.

30:02.322 --> 30:05.412
[Groans]

30:05.455 --> 30:08.154
What...

30:08.197 --> 30:09.895
What is this?
What are these notes?

30:09.938 --> 30:11.984
It says
"Good Cod Bad Cod."

30:12.027 --> 30:13.637
Are these babies?

30:13.681 --> 30:16.553
Oh, so that's how
you wanna play it, huh?!

30:16.597 --> 30:19.556
I know you're trying to start
a family without me, Kevin!

30:19.600 --> 30:21.907
Have you even thought about
what this'll do to the band?!

30:21.950 --> 30:23.865
You may as well have named
the baby Yoko!

30:23.909 --> 30:26.128
Aah!

30:26.172 --> 30:28.217
This is --

30:28.261 --> 30:30.045
Wait, is --

30:30.089 --> 30:32.178
Allison?
Oh, yeah, yeah.

30:32.221 --> 30:34.310
Sure, you didn't know
about any of this.

30:34.354 --> 30:36.791
Of course not.

30:36.835 --> 30:38.184
Oh.

30:38.227 --> 30:39.707
I never want babies.

30:39.750 --> 30:41.013
They get to sleep
whenever they want,

30:41.056 --> 30:42.449
and I think that's unfair.

30:42.492 --> 30:43.972
Th-- That's what
I thought.

30:44.016 --> 30:47.236
Well, then I've made
a huge mistake, huh?

30:47.280 --> 30:48.759
No, Neil, it's, uh...

30:48.803 --> 30:51.197
It's good
you brought this to me.

30:51.240 --> 30:53.982
Why would Allison go to
the vaginacologist without you?

30:56.071 --> 30:58.160
Why indeed, Neil.

30:58.204 --> 31:01.729
Why, indeed.

31:01.772 --> 31:04.253
Don't take that sleuthing hat
off just yet.

31:04.297 --> 31:06.429
We've got a case
to crack.

31:06.473 --> 31:08.562
The music will
have to wait!

31:10.694 --> 31:12.218
That's a solidly
built guitar.

31:12.261 --> 31:13.741
Let's go!

31:13.784 --> 31:15.525
[Laughter]

31:18.224 --> 31:19.965
Bob: Allison.

31:20.008 --> 31:21.575
I'm gonna need you
to walk us through today,

31:21.618 --> 31:22.968
before the shooting.

31:23.011 --> 31:24.621
Tammy: I know it's hard,

31:24.665 --> 31:26.014
but really,
I'm your friend here.

31:26.058 --> 31:28.103
We're almost done.

31:28.147 --> 31:31.411
Did you notice anything
outside of your usual routine?

31:31.454 --> 31:33.804
No.

31:33.848 --> 31:37.983
I woke up. I-I went to work
at the diner -- Bev's.

31:38.026 --> 31:42.422
And, yeah,
there was nothing unusual there.

31:45.468 --> 31:47.557
Just, uh, let me know
if I can get you anything else.

31:47.601 --> 31:50.256
Yeah.
We ordered two coffees.

31:50.299 --> 31:51.910
Of course.
Okay.

31:51.953 --> 31:53.520
Yeah. One sec.

31:53.563 --> 31:55.043
[Groans]

31:57.524 --> 31:59.961
Um, two coffees,
when you have a sec.

32:00.005 --> 32:02.094
Whatever you want.

32:11.059 --> 32:12.931
[Sighs]

32:12.974 --> 32:15.585
You okay?

32:15.629 --> 32:17.544
I'm fine.

32:20.677 --> 32:21.940
Hey, wait.

32:26.596 --> 32:28.120
I know it's been a hard week
for both of us,

32:28.163 --> 32:29.425
but, um...

32:29.469 --> 32:31.775
we can still talk,
you know?

32:31.819 --> 32:33.647
And if you're in a bad place,
then --

32:33.690 --> 32:36.215
Hmm?

32:36.258 --> 32:38.391
I just don't like the idea
of you drinking alone.

32:38.434 --> 32:40.001
I've tried
to find answers

32:40.045 --> 32:41.394
in the bottom
of a rocks glass, too,

32:41.437 --> 32:42.743
and I can tell you,
it doesn't work.

32:42.786 --> 32:44.745
I-I wasn't --
I wasn't drinking alone.

32:44.788 --> 32:48.053
I had some wine
with a friend last night.

32:48.096 --> 32:49.532
Oh.

32:49.576 --> 32:52.144
I'm not, like,
drowning my sorrows.

32:52.187 --> 32:53.319
Of course.

32:53.362 --> 32:54.320
I am fine.

32:54.363 --> 32:56.148
I'm, uh...

32:56.191 --> 32:58.237
happy, even.

32:58.280 --> 32:59.586
Great.

32:59.629 --> 33:01.414
Yeah.

33:01.457 --> 33:02.981
Me, too.

33:05.635 --> 33:06.854
Okay.

33:06.897 --> 33:08.464
'Kay.

33:19.040 --> 33:22.304
[Car alarm beeps]

33:22.348 --> 33:24.524
[Sighs]

33:26.700 --> 33:29.877
[Door closes]

33:29.920 --> 33:30.878
Hey.

33:32.836 --> 33:35.883
We were going to wait,
but Mom was hungry.

33:35.926 --> 33:38.146
But we understand.

33:38.190 --> 33:40.148
You're busy
at your little cafe.

33:45.197 --> 33:47.373
[Sighs]

34:00.864 --> 34:03.954
What?

34:03.998 --> 34:05.347
What "what?"

34:05.391 --> 34:06.957
You're moping.

34:07.001 --> 34:09.438
I'm just...

34:09.482 --> 34:11.571
I'm sorry I was late.

34:11.614 --> 34:14.095
Well, [Sighs] they were
just giving me a hard time

34:14.139 --> 34:16.315
about the reno
before you got here.

34:16.358 --> 34:17.707
Sorry.

34:17.751 --> 34:20.536
I should've been here
to back you up.

34:20.580 --> 34:22.147
It's okay.

34:22.190 --> 34:23.235
[Sighs]

34:23.278 --> 34:25.150
Should've expected it.

34:25.193 --> 34:26.629
I mean, they always
need something to pick at

34:26.673 --> 34:28.457
that isn't
their marriage.

34:28.501 --> 34:30.155
Why get divorced
if you can just

34:30.198 --> 34:34.289
throw money at projects
to distract yourself?

34:34.333 --> 34:35.247
You think
they should've?

34:35.290 --> 34:36.552
Uh, yeah.

34:36.596 --> 34:38.206
A long time ago.

34:38.250 --> 34:40.426
Instead of taking their hatred
for each other out

34:40.469 --> 34:41.992
on everybody else.

34:42.036 --> 34:44.125
[Laughs]
God, yes.

34:44.169 --> 34:46.040
You know, sometimes,

34:46.084 --> 34:47.911
I feel like I borrowed money
from a loan shark,

34:47.955 --> 34:49.348
the way your mom "naturally"

34:49.391 --> 34:51.393
works the diner's profit
into conversations.

34:51.437 --> 34:53.700
Can't see through that
at all.

34:53.743 --> 34:55.136
And then your dad pretends

34:55.180 --> 34:57.138
like he's on everyone's side,
right?

34:57.182 --> 34:58.618
"Dearest, please.

34:58.661 --> 35:01.142
We mustn't talk finances
in front of the children."

35:01.186 --> 35:03.188
Would've been less painful
to borrow money

35:03.231 --> 35:05.799
from someone
who'd just break my fingers.

35:09.977 --> 35:11.718
What?
[Sighs]

35:11.761 --> 35:13.154
What?

35:13.198 --> 35:14.851
They're...

35:14.895 --> 35:16.853
very generous with us.

35:16.897 --> 35:20.030
And where are your parents
any time we need anything?

35:20.074 --> 35:21.989
Okay, that's not --
I'm just agreeing with you.

35:22.032 --> 35:24.513
They've taken us to the Bahamas
every Christmas

35:24.557 --> 35:25.732
for how many years?

35:25.775 --> 35:29.692
And that's very nice
of them.

35:29.736 --> 35:32.217
But I never asked
for the Bahamas.

35:32.260 --> 35:34.567
[Sighs] They just
want us to be happy.

35:34.610 --> 35:36.482
And we wouldn't afford
this kitchen without them,

35:36.525 --> 35:38.048
let alone yourkitchen.

35:38.092 --> 35:40.703
Oh, you mean the, uh,
"little cafe" they funded?

35:40.747 --> 35:42.966
Stop it.You think they'll ever let me
be proud of that place?

35:43.010 --> 35:45.273
Of building anything,
knowing it came from them?

35:45.317 --> 35:47.362
I'm just their latest thing
to throw money at.

35:47.406 --> 35:51.279
Well, let's be honest,
you're a hell of a project!

35:51.323 --> 35:53.151
[Scoffs]

35:53.194 --> 35:55.153
[Clears throat]

36:00.723 --> 36:03.204
Where are
you going?!

36:03.248 --> 36:05.511
Maybe I don't want
to waste the next 15 years

36:05.554 --> 36:07.513
trying to distract myself.

36:10.255 --> 36:11.169
[Door slams]

36:14.955 --> 36:17.218
Is that it?

36:17.262 --> 36:19.002
Can I please go now?

36:19.046 --> 36:21.788
Mm, just about.

36:21.831 --> 36:25.270
What was Kevin doing today
up to the shooting?

36:25.313 --> 36:27.446
[Sighs]

36:27.489 --> 36:28.969
♪

36:29.012 --> 36:32.233
The human body's
a house of horrors.

36:32.277 --> 36:34.235
I just got a new
recurring nightmare.

36:34.279 --> 36:37.499
Being so small I get sucked down
my shower drain is out.

36:37.543 --> 36:40.459
That thing is in.

36:40.502 --> 36:42.243
What kind of a sicko
would choose

36:42.287 --> 36:45.377
to do this
to themselves?

36:45.420 --> 36:47.074
Oh. Sorry, ma'am.

36:47.117 --> 36:49.250
He didn't mean you.

36:49.294 --> 36:50.904
He -- He meant her.

36:50.947 --> 36:53.733
[Laughter]

36:53.776 --> 36:56.039
God, if this is all so gross,
why are we here at all?

36:56.083 --> 36:57.476
It's simple, Neil.

36:57.519 --> 37:00.000
It's a matter
of the birds and the bees.

37:00.043 --> 37:02.220
Ooh, go slow.
This story sounds fun.

37:02.263 --> 37:04.787
See, Allison's birds
are obviously

37:04.831 --> 37:08.138
not laying their eggs properly
in her little nest.

37:08.182 --> 37:09.705
So, that's why
you think she went

37:09.749 --> 37:11.098
to the baby doctor
without you?

37:11.141 --> 37:12.360
Definitely.

37:12.404 --> 37:14.144
But if these quacks
get in her head,

37:14.188 --> 37:16.756
she might try pinning herissues
on mybees.

37:16.799 --> 37:19.454
[Gasps] She wouldn't.She would.

37:19.498 --> 37:22.196
But now, she can't,
because once I go in the back

37:22.240 --> 37:23.371
and buzz in a little cup,

37:23.415 --> 37:25.068
I'll have legal
documentation

37:25.112 --> 37:29.247
showing that my dude-hive
is loaded with primo pollen.

37:29.290 --> 37:30.552
The primo-est.

37:30.596 --> 37:32.032
That's so smart.

37:32.075 --> 37:33.381
It makes perfect sense.

37:33.425 --> 37:34.687
Plus, as a bonus,

37:34.730 --> 37:36.645
they got dirty magazines
back there.

37:36.689 --> 37:39.518
Well, can't you just, like,
watch nudie stuff on your phone?

37:39.561 --> 37:41.998
Where's your sense
of history, Neil?!

37:42.042 --> 37:45.045
These are magazines, okay?
Old school.

37:45.088 --> 37:47.308
It'll be like visiting
Colonial Williamsburg

37:47.352 --> 37:50.180
and churning
my own butter.

37:50.224 --> 37:53.532
It's an enriching
experience.

37:53.575 --> 37:56.448
You always find a way
to see the magic in the world.

37:56.491 --> 37:57.710
[Laughter]

37:57.753 --> 37:58.972
♪

37:59.015 --> 38:00.278
Attention, everyone!

38:00.321 --> 38:03.150
Report to the living room
at once!

38:03.193 --> 38:05.065
[Softly] Ow.

38:05.108 --> 38:08.373
Report to the living room!
This is urgent!

38:08.416 --> 38:10.505
The last time you claimed
something was urgent,

38:10.549 --> 38:11.898
you had a fake
doctor's note

38:11.941 --> 38:15.815
claiming you had
a "meatball sub deficiency".

38:15.858 --> 38:18.034
You knew that
was fake?

38:18.078 --> 38:19.732
Listen,
none of that matters now.

38:19.775 --> 38:21.516
I have an announcement.

38:21.560 --> 38:25.694
[Drum roll]

38:25.738 --> 38:27.348
Kevin, focus!

38:27.392 --> 38:29.785
Hey!
Sorry.

38:29.829 --> 38:35.530
I, Kevin Garnett McRoberts,
am going to be a daddy.

38:35.574 --> 38:38.446
Oh, my God!
Oh, this is so exciting!

38:38.490 --> 38:41.493
What a blessing!
Oh, my child. Oh --

38:41.536 --> 38:43.538
What? No. What?
I'm not pregnant!

38:43.582 --> 38:44.931
Allison's right, Dad.

38:44.974 --> 38:46.976
There is no bun
in this roomy oven just yet.

38:47.020 --> 38:48.326
But don't worry.

38:48.369 --> 38:49.979
There will be plenty
of tummy touching

38:50.023 --> 38:51.154
down the road.

38:51.198 --> 38:52.721
Kevin,
what kind of joke is this?

38:52.765 --> 38:54.244
A cosmic one, really.

38:54.288 --> 38:55.724
I never wanted
to be a father.

38:55.768 --> 38:57.596
You know what I say
about kids --

38:57.639 --> 38:59.598
they're only good
for their tiny fingers.Tiny fingers.

38:59.641 --> 39:00.555
Exactly.

39:00.599 --> 39:01.948
And I'm all set there,

39:01.991 --> 39:03.558
'cause your hands
are pretty small.

39:03.602 --> 39:05.778
That's sweet.

39:05.821 --> 39:08.650
When you have a kid,
it becomes all about them,

39:08.694 --> 39:11.914
which means it's not about me,
and that sucks.

39:11.958 --> 39:13.438
You were a blessing,
Kevin.

39:13.481 --> 39:15.657
You never caused me
a problem once.

39:15.701 --> 39:17.137
Well, thanks,
but that's 'cause

39:17.180 --> 39:18.834
you were drunk off
the blood of Christ, Pop.

39:18.878 --> 39:23.404
But I took my talents
to the baby batter bank.

39:23.448 --> 39:25.275
The what now?

39:25.319 --> 39:27.495
The fartility clinic.

39:27.539 --> 39:29.497
And I found out

39:29.541 --> 39:32.631
that my bees have
99% motility.

39:32.674 --> 39:34.676
[Laughs]

39:34.720 --> 39:36.156
Runs in the family,
son.

39:36.199 --> 39:37.723
Yeah, when I got
your mom pregnant,

39:37.766 --> 39:40.769
we were in separate bathtubs,
like that Cialis commercial.

39:40.813 --> 39:43.511
[Laughter]

39:43.555 --> 39:45.687
Oh, come on!

39:45.731 --> 39:47.689
It would be a slap
in God's face

39:47.733 --> 39:50.649
if I only used my business
for recreational purposes.

39:50.692 --> 39:52.172
No.

39:52.215 --> 39:54.957
I need to populate this town
with mini-Kevins,

39:55.001 --> 39:57.133
for the good
of all mankind.

39:57.177 --> 39:58.657
That's my boy.So cool.

39:58.700 --> 39:59.701
No joke?

39:59.745 --> 40:00.833
No joke, babe.

40:00.876 --> 40:02.443
[Sobs]

40:02.487 --> 40:04.445
Oh, I know.
I know.

40:04.489 --> 40:06.882
All your dreams
are coming true.

40:06.926 --> 40:09.145
[Laughter][Neil and Pete baby talk]

40:09.189 --> 40:11.147
Again,
there's nothing in there!

40:11.191 --> 40:13.454
Not yet!
Not yet!

40:13.498 --> 40:15.891
But time is of the essence,
because, you know,

40:15.935 --> 40:17.502
the band is starting
to really take off,

40:17.545 --> 40:19.504
and we need to get
this going now.

40:19.547 --> 40:22.202
How awesome would it be
if we got you preggo

40:22.245 --> 40:24.073
before you left town
next week?

40:24.117 --> 40:26.467
You could celebrate
the good news with your mom!

40:26.511 --> 40:29.078
So, you're saying
you want to...

40:29.122 --> 40:30.428
like, right now?

40:30.471 --> 40:32.473
[Chuckles] Rrow!

40:32.517 --> 40:34.736
No. Not right now.

40:34.780 --> 40:36.172
No,
Jenny McCarthy Tank Top

40:36.216 --> 40:37.478
has our inaugural concert
tonight,

40:37.522 --> 40:39.001
so we have to get ready.

40:39.045 --> 40:42.265
But after the concert,
I'm all yours, hon.

40:42.309 --> 40:43.702
You know what?

40:43.745 --> 40:47.445
You'll be like
my little at-home groupie.

40:47.488 --> 40:50.535
I still can't believe it!
I'm gonna be a daddy!

40:50.578 --> 40:53.059
[Chanting]
D-A-D-D-Y!

40:53.102 --> 40:54.756
Men: [Chanting]
D-A-D-D-Y!

40:54.800 --> 40:57.455
D-A-D-D-Y!

40:57.498 --> 41:00.501
♪

41:00.545 --> 41:03.417
♪ Jenny McCarthy
Tank Top ♪

41:03.461 --> 41:05.288
[Laughs]

41:05.332 --> 41:09.031
What an amazing night!
[Laughs]

41:09.075 --> 41:13.340
What an amazing night!

41:13.383 --> 41:15.473
Aah!Oh.

41:15.516 --> 41:17.736
Oh, I just had

41:17.779 --> 41:19.781
the most amazing night
of my entire life.

41:19.825 --> 41:21.174
[Chuckles] Oh.

41:21.217 --> 41:23.655
The crowd demanded
three karaoke encores

41:23.698 --> 41:26.048
of "Don't Stop Believing."

41:26.092 --> 41:27.528
You should've
been there.

41:27.572 --> 41:28.747
Although if you had been,

41:28.790 --> 41:30.270
it might've changed the vibe
a little.

41:30.313 --> 41:32.011
Sure.

41:32.054 --> 41:35.231
Can you imagine how much people
are gonna love our band

41:35.275 --> 41:37.712
once we actually
have original songs?

41:37.756 --> 41:40.410
Or learn to play
instruments?

41:40.454 --> 41:43.370
So much.
[Sighs]

41:43.413 --> 41:45.981
Well, time for bed.

41:46.025 --> 41:48.549
We both know how you are
when you've had liquor.

41:48.593 --> 41:49.768
Oh, no, no, no, no.

41:49.811 --> 41:51.944
No, ma'am.
Not tonight.

41:51.987 --> 41:53.554
In the spirit of being
a good daddy,

41:53.598 --> 41:55.643
I have not had
a drop to drink.

41:55.687 --> 41:58.428
Just six Red Bulls.
[Giggles]

41:58.472 --> 42:00.561
[Sighs] I'll tell you,

42:00.605 --> 42:04.347
all this talk of drugs
and rock 'n' roll

42:04.391 --> 42:07.220
has really got me thinking,
you know,

42:07.263 --> 42:11.441
there's something missing
from that trifecta.

42:11.485 --> 42:12.921
I don't know.

42:12.965 --> 42:14.967
Maybe tonight is the night
that we start --

42:15.010 --> 42:17.883
[Glass shatters]What was that?

42:17.926 --> 42:20.276
I think it's just
the house settling.

42:20.320 --> 42:21.887
Well, it sounded
like more than that.

42:21.930 --> 42:23.628
[Rattling]

42:23.671 --> 42:24.672
Okay.

42:24.716 --> 42:26.979
There's someone
in the house.

42:27.022 --> 42:28.894
You stay there.Oh, this can't be happening.

42:28.937 --> 42:30.548
This can't be
happening.

42:30.591 --> 42:33.463
Kev, I'm sure it's fine --
Is that a gun?

42:33.507 --> 42:35.335
Where the hell
did you get that?

42:35.378 --> 42:38.425
I found it out in the back yard
with Neil's metal detector.

42:38.468 --> 42:39.731
The last tenant
must have buried it out there

42:39.774 --> 42:41.689
before he went to prison.

42:41.733 --> 42:44.213
But it's ours now.

42:44.257 --> 42:47.260
[Thudding]

42:47.303 --> 42:50.045
Here's the thing --
once you decide to have kids,

42:50.089 --> 42:53.353
there's this thing
that, like, awakens in you.

42:53.396 --> 42:57.052
You know? Like, a real...
protective urge.

42:57.096 --> 42:58.619
When I found this thing,
I-I didn't know

42:58.663 --> 43:00.099
what I was gonna do with it,

43:00.142 --> 43:01.579
but now...

43:01.622 --> 43:03.493
I know exactly
what it's for.

43:03.537 --> 43:05.887
I have to protect us.

43:05.931 --> 43:07.585
All of us.

43:07.628 --> 43:09.804
There's still nothing
in there.
Right. Sorry.

43:09.848 --> 43:11.327
Stay here.
Kev, don't --

43:11.371 --> 43:14.374
Shh!
Don't.

43:14.417 --> 43:16.637
[Softly] No. No, no, no.

43:16.681 --> 43:18.639
No, no, no.
[Breathing shakily]

43:18.683 --> 43:20.772
[Gunshot][Gasps]

43:21.555 --> 43:23.601
[Upbeat tune plays]

43:23.644 --> 43:24.950
Are you like okay?

43:24.993 --> 43:26.212
Do I not look okay?

43:26.255 --> 43:28.257
[Thud]

43:28.301 --> 43:29.911
We don't take
shootings lightly.

43:29.955 --> 43:31.652
You may not want to go
out of town, at all.

43:31.696 --> 43:33.175
I just don't get a good
feeling off her.

43:33.219 --> 43:34.176
[Doorbell rings]

43:34.220 --> 43:35.482
Can I, uh, come in?

43:35.525 --> 43:36.875
Inside here?

43:36.918 --> 43:38.180
What am I supposed to do,
just sit around

43:38.224 --> 43:39.529
and hope everything
works out?

43:39.573 --> 43:41.009
Cops been trying
to get in here,

43:41.053 --> 43:42.184
but I know my rights.

43:42.228 --> 43:43.925
Just need to act fast.

43:43.969 --> 43:47.886
♪
